<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Soviet-Afghanistan     09-26 0136</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Soviet-Afghanistan,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviets Report 21 Dead In Afghan Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Afghan guerrillas killed 21 people and wounded 33
today in rocket attacks on Kabul, the Afghan capital, and the city
of Pulialam to the south, the official Soviet news agency Tass said.
   The agency said 16 people were killed in a ground-to-ground
missile attack on Kabul and five died when missiles were fired in
Pulialam.
   Tass said 27 people were wounded in the Kabul attack. Six others
were injured by the shelling in Pulialam, the report said. It said
Afghan forces confiscated rocket launchers, a rifle, a mortar and
several machine guns.
   The Soviet Union began pulling its troops out of Afghanistan on
May 15. The troops were sent into the country in December 1979 to
help the Afghan government fight Moslem guerrillas.
</TEXT>
