<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--CathedralBurglary     09-26 0183</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Cathedral Burglary,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Burglary At St. Patrick's Cathedral</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A burglar who may have spent the night hiding in
locked St. Patrick's Cathedral stole cash from a collection box and
escaped before dawn Monday, one week after a killing in the
landmark church, police said.
   Capt. Barry Noxon said two janitors saw the man breaking into
the box at about 4 a.m. They did not see him leave but police were
unable to find him, Noxon said.
   The doors were locked at the time of the burglary and Noxon said
detectives suspect the man stayed inside since Sunday.
   Noxon said ``it doesn't appear he got away with very much.''
   Cardinal John J. O'Connor, who lives in the attached rectory,
was assigned around-the-clock police protection last week after a
deranged naked man killed an usher in the cathedral. The assailant
was killed by a police bullet.
   In February 1987, two men ransacked O'Connor's bedroom and
private office while he was out of town. Two armed men stole $7,000
from cathedral ushers on Nov. 30, 1985, said archdiocese spokesman
Joseph Zwilling.
</TEXT>
