<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   When actor Peter Fonda got into an argument with
a limousine driver Monday en route to O'Hare International Airport,
police were called.
   But by the time officers arrived, the two were ``kissing
cousins,'' a policeman said.
   The altercation apparently began in the limousine and police
were asked to stop the vehicle as it neared O'Hare, said Officer
Tom Legittino.
   The limo was stopped, but police said the two had resolved their
differences.
   There was a ``lack of communication between the limousine driver
and Peter Fonda,'' Legittino said, adding he was uncertain of the
nature of the argument.
   No arrests were made and no charges filed.
   The limousine company did not immediately return telephone calls.
