<1ST_LINE>u a AM-GangRape 1stLd-Writethru a0698 09-26 0672</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Gang Rape, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0698,0692</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Defendant Says He And Victim Were Having Affair</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with defendant's testimony; no pickup;
note contents.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOEL WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   One of 10 men accused in the alleged
gang rape of a woman testified Monday he was having an affair with
her and that she insisted on having sex with him outside a shed
where an illegal cockfight was taking place.
   ``She had been drinking,'' said Orlando Garza, 24, who testified
that he and the woman had been seeing each other for about two
months.
   His testimony before more than 160 people in the jammed
courtroom conflicted with the woman's allegations. The woman told
police she was abducted and raped the night of March 26-27 by as
many as 23 men at a ranch where the cockfight was taking place and
in two other locations near this southern Texas town about 50 miles
west of Corpus Christi.
   Garza is the first of the 10 men charged in the case to come to
trial, before State District Judge Ricardo Garcia.
   Garza testified he first saw the woman that night as he was
driving down a street near her home. She flagged down his pickup
truck, got in and they drove somewhere and had sex, he said.
   The woman told him she wanted to see him later that night, but
he declined because he was going to the cockfight, Garza said.
Then, as he and three friends were were driving to the ranch for
the fight, they passed the woman, who insisted on getting in, Garza
said.
   The woman testified earlier she declined to get in the car and
that ``they grabbed me and pushed me in the car.''
   When they got to ranch, Garza said his three companions got out
of the car, but the woman insisted Garza stay.
   ``I wanted to go over there (to the shed) to see the roosters,
but she wouldn't let me,'' Garza said. ``She started kissing me and
we started making love in the car.''
   Afterward, he said he went to the cockfight while she stayed in
the car. He returned later and told her he was going to take her
home because ``she was all crazy,'' Garza said.
   But she got out and followed him to the front of the car, he
said.
   ``Then she started kissing me again and we started making love
on the hood of the car,'' Garza testified.
   Garza said the woman refused to get off the car when the other
men started coming out of the shed.
   He said she finally jumped onto the hood of another car and he
and the three other men left and he went home.
   Garza said when he left she was not having sex with anybody.
   Assistant District Attorney Rodolfo Gutierrez, on cross
examination, pointed out that others had testified Garza was
present when various men were having sex with the woman, and that
Garza and another man assaulted her simultaneously.
   ``And all these people are lying, right?'' Gutierrez asked.
   Garza answered, ``Yes.''
   Garza also denied holding her wrists and having oral or anal sex
with the woman, as other witnesses have testified.
   Earlier Monday, a justice of the peace testified the woman was
dazed and crying when he interviewed her the morning after the
alleged attack.
   ``She was quiet and, you know, she would be facing down most of
the time, facing the floor,'' said Justice of the Peace Amado
Garcia Jr.
   The justice of the peace said the woman, 19, and her husband,
23, filed complaints the morning of March 27. The couple cried
during their interview, Garcia testified.
   ``Sometimes she told me they were all over her and sometimes she
didn't see who it was,'' Garcia testified.
   All 10 men charged with sexual assault are being tried
individually while those charged with kidnapping will be tried in
groups, officials have said. All 10 men have pleaded innocent. A
14-year-old boy also faces charges in the case.
</TEXT>
