<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Argentina-Plane     09-26 0222</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Argentina-Plane,0229</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Jetliner Skids Off Runway During Landing; 6 Reported Hurt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>USHUAIA, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Aerolineas Argentinas Boeing 737
skidded off the runway while landing at Ushuaia on Monday and the
state-run Telam news agency said the co-pilot, two flight
attendants and three passengers were hurt.
   The attorney general's office in Buenos Aires said a federal
judge and two federal prosecutors among several passengers who
suffered minor injuries.
   The airline, however, issued a statement saying 56 passengers
were aboard and that neither they nor any of the flight crew were
injured in the incident at this small town 2,000 miles south of the
capital city of Buenos Aires.
   Attempts to reconcile differences in the accounts proved
unavailing.
   Telam gave the number of passengers aboard as 120 and cited the
local radio station LRA 10 Radio Nacional de Ushuaia as saying
several passengers and flight crew were injured. Telam said victims
were treated at Ushuaia Hospital for concussions, fractures and
other injuries.
   The landing on the short runway lodged between mountains and the
Beagle Channel took place during severe crosswinds, Telam reported.
The agency said one wing cracked before the plane came to rest at
the edge of the channel.
   Flight 648 departed Buenos Aires at 6:30 a.m. and made two stops
before landing at Ushuaia at 11:35 a.m., Telam reported.
</TEXT>
