<HEAD>President Seeks Money for Transition</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan on Monday proposed making $2
million available to pay for the transition from his administration
to that of his White House successor.
   In a move that is subject to congressional approval, Reagan said
