<1ST_LINE>r p AM-BodyLanguage     09-26 0299</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Body Language,320</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Body Language Expert Sees Bush Warm, Believable; Dukakis Cold,
Emotionless</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CARL HILLIARD</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOULDER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   George Bush appeared believable and warm
and Michael Dukakis seemed cold, calculating and expressionless,
the traits seen in poker players or negotiators, a body language
expert said a day after the two clashed in their first debate.
   ``I've been disappointed throughout the campaign because there
hasn't been much body language to watch,'' said Judy Riggenbach, a
communications expert who advises businessmen and others about
leadership through verbal and non-verbal language.
   Sunday night's debate provided little more information; both men
restricted by podiums and microphones.
   But there was enough to see to form an opinion.
   ``What I've drawn is that Bush is more believable and credible.
He is much more animated than Dukakis. I didn't see any expression
in Dukakis' eyes. His eyes are very cold. They just don't express
anything.''
   Bush's eyes, however, were expressive.
   ``They twinkled, they sparkled, and in addition, Bush looked at
his audience and his questioners,'' she said. ``Dukakis looked at
the camera and hardly ever changed his eye focus or the position of
his head. He was almost like a robot.''
   Riggenbach, 42, who teaches speech and drama, confesses to being
a registered Republican but ``in between'' and objective in
observing political candidates.
   Dukakis limited his gestures. Bush was expansive, she observed.
   ``Dukakis had two gestures, one with one fist clenched, the
other with both fists clenched and his arms tightly to his sides.
   ``Another gesture was the use of the half-palm, that is, if you
put your palm up, then the fingers inward a quarter-rotation _ that
was his other gesture.''
   Palms down is negative, palms up is positive, she said.
   Bush, she observed, was animated and ``very fluid.''
</TEXT>
