<HEAD>Singer Recuperating From Surgery, Resumes Tour Saturday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PONTIAC, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rock singer Pat Benatar underwent
emergency abdominal surgery on the eve of a scheduled concert but
is recuperating well and will resume her national tour Saturday in
Atlanta, her publicist said.
   Benatar, 35, and her family are staying with relatives at an
unknown location while she rests in preparation for resuming the
tour, Jocelynn Loebl said in New York.
   ``She's with her husband, Neil (Geraldo), and her baby,'' Loebl
said Monday.
   Benatar was in the Detroit area on Friday for a performance at
the Pine Knob Music Center when she became ill, Loebl said.
   ``After experiencing severe abdominal pain ... Benatar was take
to Pontiac Osteopathic Hospital, where she underwent emergency
abdominal surgery,'' Loebl said. Loebl said she didn't know the
nature of the ailment but said it wasn't appendicitis as had been
reported.
   Benatar, whose nationwide tour coincides with release of her
album, ``Wide Awake in Dreamland,'' will reschedule appearances she
missed in Detroit, Chicago, Cincinnati and Columbus, Ohio, Loebl
said. No dates have been set.
