<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 0.4 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.957 million tons in
the week ended Sept. 24, an increase of 0.4 percent from the
previous week's 1.949 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 91.8 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 91.4 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
73.550 million net tons, an increase of 17.7 percent from the
62.474 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.7 percent of capacity,
compared with 76.2 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Sept. 24: Northeast
Coast, 279,000; Pittsburgh, 201,000; Youngstown, 100,000; Lake
Erie, 146,000; Detroit, 163,000; Chicago, 531,000; Midwest,
199,000; Southern, 242,000; and Western, 96,000.
