<TEXT>
   An investment group aligned with Macmillan Inc.
management said Monday it was considering amending its $2.36
billion buyout bid for the publishing concern, but a deadline
passed without an announcement.
   The British publisher Robert Maxwell has made a competing offer
of $2.41 billion in cash for all of the company's stock, but
Macmillan's board has taken no position on it and said it wanted
