<2ND_LINE>AM-Ford Production,0218</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ford Raises Fourth-Quarter Production for Third Time</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. has scheduled the third increase
in car production for the fourth quarter _ raising its total by
23,000 cars to 455,000, a company spokesman said Monday.
   On July 1, Ford projected a fourth-quarter output of 382,000
cars, but has raised production three times since then, with the
latest increase coming last Friday, spokesman Ray Windecker said.
   ``We expect the remainder of the year to continue at good to
very good sales rates,'' said Robert L. Rewey, Ford vice president
of sales operations. ``To back up that projection we have, in the
past 90 days, added 73,000 cars to our fourth-quarter U.S.
production schedule.''
   Windecker said Ford quarterly sales of several models had been
surprisingly high, helping create an increase.
   Sales of the luxury Lincoln Continental nearly have tripled from
the June 21-Sept. 20 periods of 1987 and 1988, from 3,105 last year
to 9,105 this year.
   Also, Mustang and Probe sales for the period were up from 39,178
in 1987 to 61,314 this year, while Tempo and Topaz sales went from
60,677 to 95,182 this year, Windecker said.
   However, he said, there were no planned layoffs that would be
affected by the production increase.
</TEXT>
